column4: "dougmck@pipeline.com.au Jessica Williams plays a great solo piano version of this on her Maybeck Hall CD\012"
"Using thumb and forefinger to 'drum' on one note - sus pedal down."
"Arpeggio on F7sus - finishing with surround tones of tonic"
"Ascending run is F mixolydian(Bb Maj scale) finishing on 5th (C) after its leading tone (B)"
"Internal voice moves chromatically up from A to the b7th of Eb7 "
"scale links to 9th of Bbm7 and continues up chromatically to melody note (F)"
"'Drumming' on a note and the same note an octave down"
"Descending 8 note run on F7  - easy to finger -  G (5) Eb(3)
"More 'drum-like' patterns - this time with a repeated upper tone and other scale notes echo below."
"the two melody notes are linnked chromatically"
"Series of diatonic 4th chords from BbMaj scale"
"On C7+ the altered scale begins on the 3rd"

column5: internal line plays from B chromatically down to the 3rd (G)"

column4: "Nice voicing on C7 resolving to F 6/9"
"Same thing up a 4th to F7 resolving to Bb 6/9"
